---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - QuiKey">
    <section class="privacy-page">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="privacy-content">
                <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
                <p class="last-updated">Last updated: January 2026</p>

                <p>
                    QuiKey is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains how we handle your data.
                </p>

                <h2>1. Data Collection and Storage</h2>
                <p><strong>Local Data (stored only on your device):</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Authentication tokens (stored locally in encrypted form)</li>
                    <li>API keys (stored locally in encrypted form)</li>
                    <li>Send history and preferences</li>
                    <li>Application logs (for debugging)</li>
                    <li>AI conversation history</li>
                </ul>

                <p><strong>We do NOT store:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Your files or their contents on our servers</li>
                    <li>Your emails or attachments</li>
                    <li>Your Google account credentials</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>2. Data Handling</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Files are sent directly to Google/AI services — we do not intercept or store them.</li>
                    <li>Sensitive tokens and API keys are stored locally in encrypted form.</li>
                    <li>Logs are stored locally and can be deleted at any time.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
                <p>QuiKey connects to these services based on your actions:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Google</strong> (Gmail, Drive, Gemini) — <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
                    <li><strong>OpenAI</strong> (ChatGPT) — <a href="https://openai.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenAI Privacy Policy</a></li>
                    <li><strong>Anthropic</strong> (Claude) — <a href="https://www.anthropic.com/legal/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Anthropic Privacy Policy</a></li>
                    <li><strong>OpenRouter</strong> (optional AI routing) — <a href="https://openrouter.ai/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenRouter Privacy Policy</a></li>
                    <li><strong>CloudConvert</strong> (optional PDF conversion fallback) — <a href="https://cloudconvert.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CloudConvert Privacy Policy</a></li>
                    <li><strong>Lemon Squeezy</strong> (payments and licensing) — <a href="https://www.lemonsqueezy.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lemon Squeezy Privacy Policy</a></li>
                </ul>
                <p>All communication with third-party services uses HTTPS.</p>

                <h2>4. Optional Analytics</h2>
                <p>
                    If enabled in Settings (disabled by default), QuiKey may collect pseudonymous usage and diagnostic data (feature usage, success/failure rates, performance metrics, and error events) to help improve the app.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>A pseudonymous device identifier generated by the application is used to associate events from the same device.</li>
                    <li>Analytics may be processed by us and/or service providers (e.g., PostHog).</li>
                    <li><strong>No file contents, email contents, recipients, or attachments are included</strong> in analytics events.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>To opt out: Go to Settings → General → Disable “Send usage metrics”. You may withdraw consent at any time.</p>

                <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
                <p>You have the right to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Access your data:</strong> All data is stored locally on your Mac.</li>
                    <li><strong>Delete your data:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Preferences: Use "Reset to Defaults" in Settings.</li>
                            <li>History: Clear from the History tab.</li>
                            <li>Logs: Delete from <code>~/Library/Application Support/QuiKey/Logs</code>.</li>
                            <li>Complete removal: Uninstall the app and delete the QuiKey application support folder.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Opt out of analytics:</strong> Disable in Settings → General.</li>
                    <li><strong>Revoke Google access:</strong> Remove QuiKey from your <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Account permissions</a>.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>OAuth tokens and API keys are stored locally in encrypted form.</li>
                    <li>We do not upload your files or file contents to our servers.</li>
                    <li>All communication with third-party services uses encrypted HTTPS connections.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
                <p>
                    QuiKey is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children.
                </p>

                <h2>8. Contact</h2>
                <p>Questions about this policy? Email <a href="mailto:support@quikey.app">support@quikey.app</a></p>
                <p>See also: <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    .privacy-page {
        padding: 120px 0 60px;
        min-height: 80vh;
    }

    .privacy-content {
        max-width: 700px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .privacy-content h1 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: #1f2937;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .last-updated {
        color: #6b7280;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }

    .privacy-content h2 {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: #1f2937;
        margin-top: 2.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
        padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .privacy-content p {
        color: #4b5563;
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .privacy-content ul {
        color: #4b5563;
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        padding-left: 1.5rem;
    }

    .privacy-content li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .privacy-content a {
        color: #3b82f6;
        text-decoration: none;
    }

    .privacy-content a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
    }

    .privacy-content strong {
        color: #1f2937;
    }

    .privacy-content code {
        background: #f3f4f6;
        padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
        border-radius: 4px;
        font-size: 0.9em;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .privacy-page {
            padding: 100px 0 40px;
        }

        .privacy-content h1 {
            font-size: 2rem;
        }
    }
</style>
